    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Crankcase, Crankshaft, Connecting
        Rods, And Pistons - Connecting Rods, Pistons and Piston Rings - Check Width of Top Compression Ring Groove
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Check Width of Top Compression Ring Groove</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Top compression ring groove is a keystone design which requires measurement over gauge pins to
                    determine ring groove wear.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure>
            <graphic filename="../figd04/D0420.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Measuring Top Compression Ring Groove</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston gauge pins</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check top compression ring groove for wear as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>There are two different size gauge pins to be used as follows:</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>On old style connecting rod and piston assemblies use 3 mm (0.115 in.) gauge pins.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>On new style connecting rod and piston assemblies use 2 mm (0.082 in.) gauge pins.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Install a piston gauge pin from the piston groove wear gauge pin set into the top ring groove
                        to be measured. Piston gauge pin must be parallel.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Use an outside micrometer to measure diameter over piston gauge pins.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If measurement over the gauge pin is not within specifications, excessive piston groove wear
                        exists. Replace piston.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
